A Function That Computes Effect Sizes of Dyadic Noninvariance

dyInvarEs.Rd

This function takes a model written with dyadCFA() and fitted with lavaan() and returns d_MACS values for each indicator variable. Function is a renamed version of my dMACS_long function (https://github.com/jsakaluk/dMACS_long), which was adapted from Johannes Karl's (https://johanneskarl.netlify.com) between-groups dMACS function (https://github.com/Jo-Karl/dMACS) with his assistance.

dyInvarEs(fit.cfa)

Arguments

fit.cfa

output from a dyadCFA() configural invariance model fitted with lavaan()

Value

numeric vector of dMACS values for each indicator of a given LV

See also

dyadCFA which this function relies on

Examples

dvn <- dvn2(DRES, x_order = "sip", x_stem = "sexsat", x_delim2=".", x_item_num="\\d+", distinguish_1="1", distinguish_2="2")

config.script = dyadCFA(dvn, lvname = "SexSat",  model = "configural")
